SUBSTITUTE FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 5325
A bill to amend 2016 PA 436, entitled
"Unmanned aircraft systems act,"
(MCL 259.301 to 259.331) by adding section 8a.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 Sec. 8a. (1) Subject to subsection (3), a police officer, or a
2 private security officer employed by a facility described in
3 section 45a of chapter VII of the Michigan penal code, 1931 PA 328,
4 MCL 750.45a, may intercept, disable, or destroy an unmanned
5 aircraft that is flying in a manner that violates section 45a of
6 chapter VII of the Michigan penal code, 1931 PA 328, MCL 750.45a.
7 (2) A police officer or private security officer who
8 intercepts, disables, or destroys an unmanned aircraft under
9 subsection (1) is not liable to the owner of the unmanned aircraft
JJR H03693'25 (H-2) 4kjgod

2
1 for damage to the unmanned aircraft.
2 (3) Subsection (1) applies only to a police officer or private
3 security officer who completes federally approved training and
4 certification procedures for exercising the authority described in
5 subsection (1).
6 (4) This section applies only to the extent that this section
7 is not preempted by federal law.
